Solskjær: "I won’t sleep well because of the adrenaline but you are on to the Everton game already." #mulive

Solskjær: "He [Ronaldo] had a couple of half decent headers in the first half that could have ended up with chances but it is the mark of a true finisher that he comes alive when the chance arrives." #mulive
Solskjær: "I have seen him [Ronaldo] all day today, the way he has built himself up for this game, how focused he has been and when he gets that one chance it is a goal." #mulive

Solskjær: "He [Ronaldo] has done that [score a decisive goal] so many times. When you saw him against Ireland a [few] weeks ago he missed a penalty early, didn’t touch the ball more or less, then scored two great headers in the last two minutes." #mulive

Solskjær: "It is a massive result for the team and the spirit of the team as well. We gave ourselves a difficult job with the sending off in the last game so to get three points at home is important – now we need to get to 10 or maybe 12 to get through." #mulive
Villarreal's Pau Torres: "Cristiano is a player who gets one chance and he gets it in, and that's what's happened." #mulive [@MovistarFutbol]

Raphaël Varane on the #UCL: "We want to show our public that we can and that we want to win this competition." #mulive [mu]

Raphaël Varane: "There is no revenge spirit [from #mufc to Villarreal], they told me, of course, that they knew the opponent because they played against them, last season. But, really, we are focused on our objective, on our way to play, on our ambition." #mulive [mu]

Raphaël Varane on the #UCL: "What we need to do is to believe that we can do it at every step of the way. And we have to do so mostly during the toughest moments, which will happen at every game because it is a high-level competition." #mulive [mu]

Raphaël Varane on his #UCL experience: "I think that this experience is important to acquire tranquility in the toughest moments — to believe that this is possible. I know how hard it is to win this type of competitions but we have the potential in this team." #mulive [mu]

Raphaël Varane: "For me, the Champions League is always a special competition — all the ingredients to have a beautiful show and a big game of Champions League are gathered [against Villarreal], that is something that we all want as football players." #mulive [mu]
Solskjær: “He [Rashford] looks raring to go, happy and he knows he's missed out on pre-season, but he's done loads of good conditioning work and should be ready soon.” #mulive [mu]

Solskjær: “They're [Rashford & Amad] still a few weeks away so, hopefully after the international break — they're working hard, both of them positive, and it's been a long, long time for Marcus of course. Probably the longest he's been out but he's needed it.” #mulive [mu]
